The '''Manitoba general election''' of October 11, 1977 was held to elect Members of the [[Legislative Assembly of Manitoba|Legislative Assembly]] of the Province of [[Manitoba]], [[Canada]].  It was won by the [[Progressive Conservative Party of Manitoba|Progressive Conservative Party]], which took 33 seats out of 57.  The governing [[New Democratic Party of Manitoba|New Democratic Party]] fell to 23 seats, while the [[Manitoba Liberal Party|Liberal Party]] won only one seat.

[[Image:MB1977.PNG|200px|thumb|Map of Election Results]]

